title: For Sale:  Wake County ACLU Firearms Panel Discussion - Wednesday April 10 - Please attend if you can!
location: Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
The Wake County ACLU will host a panel discussion entitled “Firearms and Our Society” Wednesday evening, April 10, 2013, at 7:00pm. The event will be held at the Advocates For Justice Building, 1312 Annapolis Dr, Raleigh, NC. Participants will discuss various gun control related issues that are facing our society today and how these issues affect not only our society as a whole, but how they also affect our rights as gun owners.

Participants include:

    Paul Valone, President, Grass Roots North Carolina
    Carlos Mahoney, National ACLU Board Member and National ACLU Gun Control Board Member
    Earl Woodham, United States Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives (BATFE)
    Gail Neely, North Carolinians Against Gun Violence


Local media organizations will be covering the event and as you can see above, the deck is stacked against those of us who believe that the right to protect our lives should not be infringed. The topics will include the ACLU's policy-making decision process for gun control, the current gun laws and how they are enforced at the Federal level, as well as opposing views of the issues by Paul Valone and Gail Neely.

Make plans to attend!

We need your support! If at all possible, make plans to attend the event and show your unwavering support for our rights. We cannot sit idly by while political forces with seemingly bottomless pockets continue their assault on the Second Amendment. As President Obama and political forces across the country continue their assault on our rights as gun owners, the support we give for those defending our freedoms must be just as strong.

title: For Sale:  Baby Eagle Compact 9mm
postcontent:
The “Baby” of the Desert Eagle family offers an excellent handgun value and plenty of firepower. The grip design is exceptionally comfortable and well liked by shooters.

Trigger action of the Baby Desert Eagle pistol is double action/single action (DA/SA).

I bought this gun new in 2002 and have probably put around 2000 rounds through it. To be honest, I love this gun and a soft spot for it, but it hasn't always been ultra reliable. It fires about 98% of the time. To its credit, I usually run target grade ammo through it, so it could be an ammo issue. But for proper disclaimer, if I go to the range with 100 rounds, it will generally fail to fire 2 or 3 of them. Some ammo seems better, some worse. Sometimes I can go to the range and run 100 rounds with zero FTF, it really just seems like an ammo-picky gun. If you want a range gun, it's a good gun. I'm not sure I'd depend on it with my life - hence why km selling it.

It originally came with one mag, but I've picked up a couple more over the years so now it comes with 3. All of the Mags are 10-rounders, although I think our can get 12 or maybe 13 rounders if you want.

On the bright side, it is probably the most comfortable and coolest looking gun around. It's a beauty, and I hate to get rid of it.

Comes with factory carry case, lock, three 10-rd factory mags, manual, a soft brush and a wire brush. 

Require valid driver's license or State-issued ID (for positive identification), CPL, and RI-060 at sale. Local transaction only. Cash only. Public place.
